prompt:
Add location and weather context to the agent's system prompt using Open-Meteo. See issue #25.

## Context

reel-life is a media curation agent (Go, Claude API). The system prompt is built in `internal/agent/agent.go:buildSystemPrompt()`. It currently injects the date and pinned notebook notes. We want to also inject current weather and location.

## Key files

- `internal/agent/agent.go` — `Agent` struct, `buildSystemPrompt()` method (line ~108), `New()` constructor
- `internal/config/config.go` — `Config` struct, `AgentConfig`, config loading, env overrides
- `nix/module.nix` — NixOS module (uses `builtins.toJSON` for config generation)
- `cmd/reel-life/main.go` — wiring

## What to build

### 1. Weather client: `internal/weather/weather.go`

Create a simple Open-Meteo client:

```go
type Conditions struct {
    Temperature float64 // Celsius
    Description string  // human-readable (e.g. "partly cloudy")
    FetchedAt   time.Time
}

type Client struct {
    latitude  float64
    longitude float64
    location  string // display name (e.g. "Montreal, QC")
    mu        sync.RWMutex
    cached    *Conditions
    cacheTTL  time.Duration
    httpClient *http.Client
}
```

- `NewClient(latitude, longitude float64, locationName string) *Client`
- `Current(ctx context.Context) (*Conditions, error)` — returns cached if fresh (<30min), otherwise fetches
- Open-Meteo endpoint: `https://api.open-meteo.com/v1/forecast?latitude={lat}&longitude={lon}&current=temperature_2m,weather_code&timezone=auto`
- Map WMO weather codes to descriptions (0=clear, 1-3=partly cloudy, 45-48=fog, 51-55=drizzle, 61-65=rain, 71-75=snow, 80-82=showers, 95-99=thunderstorm, etc.)
- If fetch fails, return cached (even if stale) or nil — never error out, just degrade gracefully
- 30 second HTTP timeout

### 2. Config

Add to `internal/config/config.go`:

```go
type LocationConfig struct {
    Name      string  `yaml:"name"`
    Latitude  float64 `yaml:"latitude"`
    Longitude float64 `yaml:"longitude"`
}
```

Add `Location LocationConfig `yaml:"location"`` to the main Config struct.

No env var overrides needed for this — it's static config.

### 3. Integration in agent

- Add a `weather *weather.Client` field to the `Agent` struct (can be nil)
- Update `New()` and `NewWithClient()` to accept the weather client
- In `buildSystemPrompt()`, after the date line, if weather client is set:
  - Call `a.weather.Current(ctx)` — but buildSystemPrompt doesn't take ctx currently. Either pass ctx or use `context.Background()` (the cache makes this fast)
  - If conditions available, add: `"Current location: {name}. Weather: {temp}°C, {description}."`
  - If unavailable, just add: `"Current location: {name}."`

### 4. Wiring in main.go

- If `cfg.Location.Latitude != 0 || cfg.Location.Longitude != 0`, create a weather client and pass to the agent
- Otherwise, skip (no weather context)

### 5. NixOS module

Add to `nix/module.nix` options:

```nix
locationName = lib.mkOption {
  type = lib.types.str;
  default = "";
  description = "Display name for the location (e.g. Montreal, QC)";
};
locationLatitude = lib.mkOption {
  type = lib.types.float;
  default = 0.0;
  description = "Latitude for weather lookups";
};
locationLongitude = lib.mkOption {
  type = lib.types.float;
  default = 0.0;
  description = "Longitude for weather lookups";
};
```

Wire into the JSON config via `lib.optionalAttrs (cfg.locationLatitude != 0.0)`:
```nix
location = {
  name = cfg.locationName;
  latitude = cfg.locationLatitude;
  longitude = cfg.locationLongitude;
};
```

### 6. Tests

- Test WMO code → description mapping
- Test caching (mock HTTP, verify second call uses cache)
- Test graceful degradation (HTTP failure returns nil, not error)
- Test buildSystemPrompt includes weather when available
- Test buildSystemPrompt works fine when weather client is nil

### Acceptance criteria
- `go build ./...` && `go test ./...` && `go vet ./...` pass
- When location is configured, the system prompt includes location and weather
- Weather is cached for 30 minutes
- If Open-Meteo is unreachable, the agent still works (just no weather in prompt)
- NixOS module exposes location options
